# Agent delivery workflow (IAM — always on)

Same contract as in-app Agent Sam (`agentsam_rules_document:rule_agent_delivery_workflow` + `src/core/agent-delivery-workflow.js`).

**Applies when:** active workspace is an IAM build lane with a ship profile. **Two platform repos — never mix:**

| Workspace | Repo root | Deploy |
|-----------|-----------|--------|
| `inneranimalmedia` | `/Users/samprimeaux/inneranimalmedia` | `npm run deploy:full` (+ vite build when dashboard touched) |
| `inneranimalmedia-mcp` | `/Users/samprimeaux/inneranimalmedia-mcp-server` | `npm run deploy:full` from MCP repo only (`node --check src/index.js`) |
| Collab (`fuelnfreetime`, etc.) | workspace `root_path` | per workspace metadata |

**Does not apply** to unrelated workspaces without a ship profile.

## Order (unless user opts out)

1. Complete the work in **this workspace repo root only**.
2. Validate locally (repo-specific — MCP has no vite build).
3. Commit + push (why-focused message; no secrets).
4. Deploy from workspace repo root.
5. Follow up — shipped, verified, git ref, 1–3 next steps.

Opt-outs: `local only`, `no commit`, `no push`, `no deploy`, `plan only`, `review only`.

Do not ask permission to commit/deploy when no opt-out was given.
